Manchester City on Wednesday completed the signing of Leicester City defender, Camron Gbadebo. Gbadebo joined the Citizens after having a successful trial with the Premier League champions. The 17-year-old made eleven appearances for Leicester City’s Under-18. Gbadebo is an England born player with Nigerian descent. “I’m so happy to announce that I’ve signed for @mancity,” Gbadebo wrote on Instagram after completing his deal. “Thank you to everyone that has supported me on my journey so far. This is only just the beginning!”